Package org.spongepowered.api.data.manipulator.immutable

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ImmutableAttributeData
    An ImmutableDataManipulator handling an ImmutableAttributeMapValue.
    ImmutableColoredData
    An ImmutableDataManipulator for handling the Color of something such as ItemStacks, BlockTypes.WOOL, etc.
    ImmutableCommandData
    An ImmutableDataManipulator handling all related ImmutableValues for command related DataHolders, such as CommandBlocks and MinecartCommandBlocks.
    ImmutableDisplayNameData  
    ImmutableDyeableData
    An ImmutableVariantData handling the DyeColor for a DataHolder, including BlockTypes.WOOL to Sheep to Wolf.
    ImmutableFireworkData
    An ImmutableDataManipulator handling the various FireworkEffects associated with a Firework and an ItemStack that is of the ItemTypes.FIREWORKS.
    ImmutableMobSpawnerData
    An ImmutableDataManipulator for all information surrounding a MobSpawner and MinecartMobSpawner.
    ImmutableMobSpawnerData.ImmutableNextEntityToSpawnValue
    Represents a custom Value dealing with the next WeightedEntity such that the next Entity to spawn may be pulled from the owning ImmutableMobSpawnerData.possibleEntitiesToSpawn() with a default Random, or it may be custom defined on a case by case basis.
    ImmutableOwnableData
    An ImmutableDataManipulator handling the GameProfile associated with "owning" an Entity.
    ImmutablePotionEffectData
    An ImmutableDataManipulator that handles the various PotionEffects that may either affect an Entity or be contained within an ItemStack of the type ItemTypes.POTION.
    ImmutableRepresentedItemData
    An ImmutableDataManipulator handling the representation of an ItemStack.
    ImmutableRotationalData
    An ImmutableVariantData handling the Rotation of a DataHolder.
    ImmutableSkullData
    An ImmutableVariantData specializing in the SkullType represented by a Skull or ItemStack of the type ItemTypes.SKULL.
    ImmutableTargetedLocationData
    An ImmutableDataManipulator handling the supposed targetted Location.
    ImmutableVariantData<E,I extends ImmutableVariantData<E,I,M>,M extends VariantData<E,M,I>>
    Represents a type of ImmutableDataManipulator handling a specific type of element, usually CatalogTypes.
    ImmutableWetData
    An ImmutableDataManipulator that handles the "wet" state of various DataHolders that can include BlockTypes.SPONGE blocks to Wolf entities being "wet".
